title: For Sale:  German .22 snub revolver Fully polished!
postcontent:
First off I recieved this revolver in a trade and then stripped it all down . I then polished the exterior of the gun. The pics do not do justice.
This is a very unusual .22 short revolver that I believe was made in limited numbers in Germany to the importer EIG's specifications. I've never seen another like it. Description follows:

This is a lightweight snubnose revolver with a detachable hammer shroud (1 screw) which fully encloses the DAO hammer. Front of trigger guard was removed at the factory (not an aftermarket modification). Cylinder is not removable, utilizing a swing-out gate for loading and a detachable ramrod that screws into place under the barrel to push out individual brass cases. This is a 6-shot revolver stamped ".22 short". Grips are very narrow checkered black plastic with EIG logo. Mainspring is a coil, as with a Charter Arms or Ruger, rather than the typical leaf spring found on RG/Rohm revolvers. For what it is, I was surprised at how much care went into the design and manufacture of this rare variant of a Saturday Night Special "junk" gun. I have fired 12 rounds through this piece and it is fully functional and surprisingly accurate.
open to trades

Gun is in Very Good or better overall condition for what it is. 

NO BAD GUYS MUST BE 21 CODL OR CCW 
REDACTED direct to my phone

title: For Sale:  Shotgun Barrels - 250 to Choose from! R thru W
postcontent:
Here is our latest inventory. The list is too big to put on armslist at one time. See the other list: Benelli thru Mossberg. We have the largest inventory of shotgun barrels you'll ever see at most gun shows! Most barrels are refurbished to like new condition. Some are brand new! *All Subject to prior sale. Your barrel will ship immediately if you pay by PayPal. Sorry, we don't do credit/debt cards.
We will TRADE for your old beat-up barrel in most any condition. Rusty, Nasty, Bent, Bulged or Dented.

We're not a regular business. We don't have a storefront. We're just two old guys that sell shotgun parts on the weekends at gun shows. We both hold regular full-time jobs too. To atempt to keep up with demand we also BUY shotgun parts, pieces, stocks & foreends. We'll buy junker pump & auto shotguns just to get the parts. Why, we've bought four gunsmith's estates for its parts. 

M-F call Roy @ REDACTED (warehouse)
Nights/weekends, Jim @ REDACTED
We are old guys, we don't text.

See our huge display of Shotgun Barrels at mid-south gun shows! 
We will be back on the road in September.
